The paper discusses the debate over the existence of sophisticated mental grammars and the statistical approach to language learning, which are both topics within computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also touches on the cognitive aspects of language learning, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper may discuss the computational complexity of language learning, which is a topic in computer science theory (cs.CC) and cryptography (cs.CR).
